          <msContents>
            <summary>Fragment of a commentary on the Pentateuch in Judeo-Arabic, surviving at the later portions of Exodus XXV (discussion of the creation of the Ark of the Convenant on recto, and the creation of the Menorah on verso). Written in an eastern semicursive script; various sentence-style punctuations (colons, dashes, and overlines on abbreviations) throughout; 19 long lines (surviving).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="jrb">In Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
